Larry held its peak from around 12:00 UTC on September 5 to 00:00 UTC on September 6, according to the TCR. The actual peak was probably late on September 5, but there are no good colored satellite images from that time. Switching to an image that was taken slightly before the peak, since the current image is too bright, and makes the storm's features kind of hard to see. We are not mandated to use images closest to the peak.
